The paper deals with learning compressible representations in deep architectures, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The two applications showcased in the paper are image compression (cs.CV) and neural network compression (cs.AI). The paper also involves entropy coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with multimedia (cs.MM) in the context of image compression. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IT.
